1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,791
Steam has new hardware out.

2
00:00:01,791 --> 00:00:02,625
It's a controller.

3
00:00:02,625 --> 00:00:04,000
Costs $100.

4
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:06,375
Sold out everywhere within hours of release.

5
00:00:06,375 --> 00:00:07,666
I got mine by staying up late

6
00:00:07,666 --> 00:00:09,375
and frantically hitting refresh.

7
00:00:09,375 --> 00:00:10,500
It's so expensive,

8
00:00:10,500 --> 00:00:11,500
yet so popular.

9
00:00:11,500 --> 00:00:13,875
Half of that is because Steam has always had a great reputation.

10
00:00:13,875 --> 00:00:14,583
The other half is because

11
00:00:14,583 --> 00:00:16,500
it's actually quite special.

12
00:00:16,500 --> 00:00:19,333
If you're the target audience Gabe Newell has in mind,

13
00:00:19,333 --> 00:00:20,500
it might even be

14
00:00:20,500 --> 00:00:23,708
the ultimate choice surpassing all other controllers.

15
00:00:23,708 --> 00:00:25,833
So this video will tell you everything

16
00:00:25,833 --> 00:00:28,458
you need to know about the Steam Controller.

17
00:00:28,458 --> 00:00:29,666
All its features,

18
00:00:29,666 --> 00:00:30,625
and most importantly,

19
00:00:30,625 --> 00:00:32,500
whether it's worth buying.

20
00:00:36,916 --> 00:00:38,291
Looking at the design, the Steam Controller

21
00:00:38,291 --> 00:00:42,041
is a symmetrical full-featured PC controller.

22
00:00:42,041 --> 00:00:43,708
The joysticks are symmetrically placed.

23
00:00:43,708 --> 00:00:45,041
Buttons are A, B, X, Y.

24
00:00:45,041 --> 00:00:46,916
There are a few extra Steam-themed buttons.

25
00:00:46,916 --> 00:00:48,333
Four back buttons on the rear.

26
00:00:48,333 --> 00:00:50,083
No 3.5mm headphone jack.

27
00:00:50,083 --> 00:00:50,500
Oh,

28
00:00:50,500 --> 00:00:52,000
what's that?

29
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:54,083
It's a screw hole.

30
00:00:54,083 --> 00:00:55,916
Clearly easy to disassemble.

31
00:00:55,916 --> 00:00:57,833
Unlike other PC controllers,

32
00:00:57,833 --> 00:01:00,791
these two trackpads inherited from the Steam Deck

33
00:01:00,833 --> 00:01:02,000
are what make

34
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:05,000
the Steam Controller's shape square and wide.

35
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:06,000
The joystick position

36
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:09,333
is pushed to a somewhat less reachable spot.

37
00:01:09,333 --> 00:01:13,125
Here's how it looks in the hands of our colleague with large hands.

38
00:01:13,166 --> 00:01:15,250
It feels a bit tight,

39
00:01:15,250 --> 00:01:16,500
not very comfortable.

40
00:01:16,500 --> 00:01:18,041
But this hard-to-reach aspect

41
00:01:18,041 --> 00:01:19,583
for those with small hands who

42
00:01:19,583 --> 00:01:22,083
can't fully grip it anyway,

43
00:01:22,083 --> 00:01:24,000
is actually not that hard to accept.

44
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:26,500
Honestly, I got used to it pretty quickly.

45
00:01:26,500 --> 00:01:28,833
These joysticks are quite high-tech.

46
00:01:28,833 --> 00:01:30,833
They're called TMR joysticks.

47
00:01:30,833 --> 00:01:32,208
You may have heard of

48
00:01:32,208 --> 00:01:34,250
Hall effect joysticks that almost never drift.

49
00:01:34,250 --> 00:01:36,041
TMR is the next generation of Hall effect,

50
00:01:36,041 --> 00:01:37,666
more accurate and lower power consumption.

51
00:01:37,666 --> 00:01:40,083
And it hardly drifts at all.

52
00:01:40,125 --> 00:01:41,666
Probably because it's large.

53
00:01:41,666 --> 00:01:44,833
So it's heavier than a regular controller.

54
00:01:44,875 --> 00:01:47,500
The upside is extremely long battery life.

55
00:01:47,500 --> 00:01:48,250
The Steam Controller

56
00:01:48,250 --> 00:01:51,000
can last about thirty-something hours.

57
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:54,000
I feel like the PS5 controller barely lasts 6 hours.

58
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:57,041
Overall, the feel is okay.

59
00:01:57,041 --> 00:01:58,833
All buttons are membrane switches.

60
00:01:58,833 --> 00:02:00,125
The joysticks are very smooth.

61
00:02:00,125 --> 00:02:02,375
But the back buttons are a bit easy to accidentally press.

62
00:02:02,375 --> 00:02:05,500
Grip feel is better than the Steam Deck handheld.

63
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:07,916
But still a bit worse than first-party controllers.

64
00:02:07,916 --> 00:02:08,875
Build quality too.

65
00:02:08,875 --> 00:02:11,208
Surface texture is also slightly lacking.

66
00:02:11,416 --> 00:02:12,166
To be honest,

67
00:02:12,166 --> 00:02:15,416
it's like a Steam Deck with the screen cut off.

68
00:02:15,416 --> 00:02:16,041
Hehe.

69
00:02:16,041 --> 00:02:19,333
It's the opposite design philosophy of the PlayStation Portal.

70
00:02:19,708 --> 00:02:21,166
Next is compatibility.

71
00:02:21,166 --> 00:02:22,500
Steam's official statement is

72
00:02:22,500 --> 00:02:26,083
it only supports all operating systems that can install Steam.

73
00:02:26,083 --> 00:02:29,416
That means it doesn't support PS5, Switch, or Xbox.

74
00:02:29,416 --> 00:02:31,125
Nor iOS or Android.

75
00:02:31,125 --> 00:02:34,000
But it supports Windows, macOS, and Linux.

76
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:35,916
Including SteamOS, of course.

77
00:02:36,083 --> 00:02:36,875
This compatibility

78
00:02:36,875 --> 00:02:38,250
actually reflects well

79
00:02:38,250 --> 00:02:40,000
the purpose of the Steam Controller.

80
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:42,500
Most controllers are made for console games,

81
00:02:42,500 --> 00:02:44,208
with PC compatibility as an afterthought.

82
00:02:44,291 --> 00:02:45,500
But Steam wanted to make

83
00:02:45,500 --> 00:02:47,875
a controller specifically for PC games.

84
00:02:47,875 --> 00:02:51,000
So it needed things ordinary controllers don't have:

85
00:02:51,166 --> 00:02:52,000
trackpads,

86
00:02:52,083 --> 00:02:52,750
paddles,

87
00:02:52,750 --> 00:02:55,625
and the Steam Input software that ties it all together.

88
00:02:56,458 --> 00:02:57,541
The trackpads,

89
00:02:58,000 --> 00:02:58,666
at first glance,

90
00:02:58,666 --> 00:03:00,708
seem similar to the Steam Deck's trackpads,

91
00:03:00,708 --> 00:03:02,291
just a nice bonus.

92
00:03:02,291 --> 00:03:03,833
You might not use them much.

93
00:03:03,833 --> 00:03:05,000
But on Windows,

94
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:07,500
the trackpads are a lifesaver.

95
00:03:07,500 --> 00:03:08,291
The Steam Controller

96
00:03:08,291 --> 00:03:10,916
isn't actually the first controller Steam released.

97
00:03:11,625 --> 00:03:12,500
This one is.

98
00:03:12,500 --> 00:03:14,333
The trackpads are much larger,

99
00:03:14,333 --> 00:03:18,125
even squeezing out the original d-pad and joystick.

100
00:03:18,916 --> 00:03:21,125
Valve is so persistent about trackpads

101
00:03:21,125 --> 00:03:22,125
because PC games

102
00:03:22,125 --> 00:03:23,250
want to enter the living room,

103
00:03:23,250 --> 00:03:24,041
connect to the TV,

104
00:03:24,041 --> 00:03:25,583
but without a keyboard and mouse to rely on,

105
00:03:25,583 --> 00:03:28,541
the controller must handle most operations.

106
00:03:33,041 --> 00:03:34,333
Then there's the Puck,

107
00:03:34,333 --> 00:03:37,833
the small 2.4G receiver that comes with the Steam Controller.

108
00:03:37,833 --> 00:03:40,833
This thing is pucking amazing.

109
00:03:40,833 --> 00:03:43,541
It also has magnetic charging functionality.

110
00:03:43,583 --> 00:03:45,291
Input latency is much lower than Bluetooth.

111
00:03:45,291 --> 00:03:46,375
The signal is very good.

112
00:03:46,375 --> 00:03:49,000
And one Puck can connect four controllers.

113
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:50,083
Most importantly,

114
00:03:50,083 --> 00:03:51,666
the Puck combined with the touchpad

115
00:03:51,666 --> 00:03:55,791
completely changes the interaction method for Windows games in the living room.

116
00:03:55,875 --> 00:03:56,958
First step:

117
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:58,166
wake up Windows.

118
00:03:58,375 --> 00:03:59,375
In the past,

119
00:03:59,375 --> 00:04:01,458
you had to run over and press the power button.

120
00:04:01,458 --> 00:04:02,791
But the Steam Controller is different.

121
00:04:02,791 --> 00:04:03,833
By default,

122
00:04:03,833 --> 00:04:05,500
it is not recognized by the computer as a controller,

123
00:04:05,500 --> 00:04:06,500
but as a keyboard and mouse.

124
00:04:06,500 --> 00:04:08,250
And when connected via the Puck,

125
00:04:08,250 --> 00:04:09,833
it is still a USB keyboard and mouse.

126
00:04:09,833 --> 00:04:13,208
You can wake up the PC from the couch with the controller.

127
00:04:17,291 --> 00:04:18,333
Isn't that great?

128
00:04:18,333 --> 00:04:19,583
When the computer first starts up,

129
00:04:19,583 --> 00:04:20,916
the right touchpad is the mouse,

130
00:04:20,916 --> 00:04:22,291
the left touchpad is the scroll wheel,

131
00:04:22,291 --> 00:04:23,708
the left trigger is right-click,

132
00:04:23,708 --> 00:04:25,250
the right trigger is left-click,

133
00:04:25,250 --> 00:04:26,583
A is Enter,

134
00:04:26,583 --> 00:04:27,666
B is Escape,

135
00:04:27,666 --> 00:04:29,791
the D-pad corresponds to the arrow keys on the keyboard.

136
00:04:29,791 --> 00:04:30,166
At this point,

137
00:04:30,166 --> 00:04:31,291
we can perform simple operations

138
00:04:31,291 --> 00:04:32,708
in the Windows interface.

139
00:04:32,708 --> 00:04:33,416
After that,

140
00:04:33,416 --> 00:04:34,791
press the Steam button again

141
00:04:34,791 --> 00:04:36,333
to wake up Steam.

142
00:04:36,333 --> 00:04:37,416
When Steam is running,

143
00:04:37,416 --> 00:04:39,000
the controller has more functions,

144
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:40,708
such as bringing up the virtual keyboard.

145
00:04:40,708 --> 00:04:42,208
Press the Steam button again

146
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:49,000
to enter Steam Big Picture mode,

147
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:50,375
an interface similar to the Steam Deck.

148
00:04:50,375 --> 00:04:51,000
At this point,

149
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:53,791
the controller enters normal console-style interaction.

150
00:04:53,791 --> 00:04:56,583
The touchpad's mission for UI interaction is thus complete.

151
00:04:56,583 --> 00:04:58,833
If you still insist on using a mouse,

152
00:04:58,833 --> 00:05:00,750
for example, when a software pop-up appears,

153
00:05:00,833 --> 00:05:03,041
you can still hold down this... key

154
00:05:03,041 --> 00:05:04,291
to trigger the trackpad.

155
00:05:04,291 --> 00:05:05,333
You can also do this:

156
00:05:07,416 --> 00:05:08,500
switch windows.

157
00:05:08,500 --> 00:05:11,041
You can also use the trackpad to press the virtual keyboard.

158
00:05:11,041 --> 00:05:13,000
Two fingers together is quite fast.

159
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:13,875
Long press

160
00:05:14,208 --> 00:05:16,583
will show you various things you can trigger with the controller.

161
00:05:16,583 --> 00:05:17,583
Other shortcuts

162
00:05:17,583 --> 00:05:18,625
Quite a lot.

163
00:05:18,666 --> 00:05:20,375
No need to get up during the entire operation.

164
00:05:20,375 --> 00:05:22,375
This is currently the closest Windows experience

165
00:05:22,375 --> 00:05:24,458
to a plug-and-play game console.

166
00:05:24,458 --> 00:05:25,625
Once you enter the game,

167
00:05:25,625 --> 00:05:28,208
the trackpad performs similarly to the Steam Deck.

168
00:05:28,208 --> 00:05:29,041
As you slide,

169
00:05:29,041 --> 00:05:30,916
there's motor vibration feedback underneath.

170
00:05:30,916 --> 00:05:32,708
Every area can also be pressed down.

171
00:05:32,708 --> 00:05:33,291
You can play some

172
00:05:33,291 --> 00:05:35,291
strategy games designed specifically for keyboard and mouse.

173
00:05:35,291 --> 00:05:38,083
A colleague who prefers to remain anonymous said

174
00:05:38,083 --> 00:05:41,000
this trackpad is convenient for playing adult games.

175
00:05:41,166 --> 00:05:42,666
Oh, right, this trackpad

176
00:05:42,666 --> 00:05:45,125
is of course not just for use as a mouse.

177
00:05:45,125 --> 00:05:47,166
It can also be configured as other buttons,

178
00:05:47,166 --> 00:05:48,250
like keyboard keys,

179
00:05:48,250 --> 00:05:50,041
such as numbers 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6,

180
00:05:50,041 --> 00:05:51,625
for playing MMORPGs.

181
00:05:51,625 --> 00:05:53,708
It can even trigger specific in-game functions,

182
00:05:53,708 --> 00:05:55,000
like in DOOM Eternal.

183
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:57,500
Normally, switching weapons is a combination of buttons and joystick,

184
00:05:57,500 --> 00:06:00,000
but I can directly touch the trackpad

185
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:01,333
to trigger the weapon wheel.

186
00:06:01,416 --> 00:06:02,833
Release to confirm.

187
00:06:05,458 --> 00:06:06,833
Let's talk about

188
00:06:06,833 --> 00:06:10,916
the software that allows us to infinitely customize the Steam Controller,

189
00:06:10,916 --> 00:06:11,500
Steam.

190
00:06:11,500 --> 00:06:12,041
Yes,

191
00:06:12,041 --> 00:06:13,583
it's Steam itself.

192
00:06:13,583 --> 00:06:14,500
Because the Steam Controller

193
00:06:14,500 --> 00:06:16,333
is recognized as a special keyboard and mouse by default,

194
00:06:16,333 --> 00:06:17,708
you must open Steam

195
00:06:17,708 --> 00:06:19,791
for it to work like a controller.

196
00:06:19,791 --> 00:06:21,916
Steam itself is the driver for the controller.

197
00:06:21,916 --> 00:06:23,666
Steam can display the controller's battery level,

198
00:06:23,666 --> 00:06:24,625
update firmware,

199
00:06:24,625 --> 00:06:26,208
show wireless signal strength,

200
00:06:26,208 --> 00:06:28,291
and even find the controller like a lost TV remote.

201
00:06:28,291 --> 00:06:31,125
You can call up your controller in Steam

202
00:06:37,083 --> 00:06:39,166
It feels like Valve forced everyone's Steam client

203
00:06:39,166 --> 00:06:40,875
to be stuffed with a lot of junk code

204
00:06:40,875 --> 00:06:42,583
You wouldn't need it if you don't buy a controller

205
00:06:42,583 --> 00:06:43,666
Just now I was talking about customization

206
00:06:43,666 --> 00:06:45,833
I guess most people are like me

207
00:06:45,833 --> 00:06:47,083
It's too complicated

208
00:06:47,083 --> 00:06:48,125
I'm so lazy

209
00:06:48,125 --> 00:06:49,708
I just use the defaults

210
00:06:49,833 --> 00:06:52,458
But actually, you don't need to study it much

211
00:06:52,458 --> 00:06:53,500
Just use others'

212
00:06:53,500 --> 00:06:54,500
and that's it

213
00:06:54,500 --> 00:06:57,416
Because Steam Deck has sold nearly 8 million units

214
00:06:57,416 --> 00:06:59,041
So for many popular games on Steam

215
00:06:59,041 --> 00:07:00,500
a lot of people have already uploaded

216
00:07:00,500 --> 00:07:02,458
their own custom configuration files

217
00:07:02,458 --> 00:07:04,666
They're in the community configurations of controller settings

218
00:07:04,666 --> 00:07:06,250
And as soon as the Steam Controller was born

219
00:07:06,250 --> 00:07:08,500
it could directly use these ready-made ones

220
00:07:08,833 --> 00:07:09,625
For example

221
00:07:09,625 --> 00:07:11,083
The Steam Controller and Steam Deck

222
00:07:11,083 --> 00:07:11,875
like the Switch

223
00:07:11,875 --> 00:07:13,166
both have gyroscope functionality

224
00:07:13,166 --> 00:07:14,833
Allowing certain games to use the gyroscope

225
00:07:14,833 --> 00:07:16,291
for aiming in shooting games

226
00:07:16,291 --> 00:07:18,291
Compensating for the lack of precision in joysticks

227
00:07:18,375 --> 00:07:19,833
The Splatoon series is like that

228
00:07:19,833 --> 00:07:21,791
Gyro aiming is actually great

229
00:07:21,791 --> 00:07:23,625
Very close to the precision of a mouse

230
00:07:23,625 --> 00:07:24,666
And also very intuitive

231
00:07:24,666 --> 00:07:26,583
But not many games support it

232
00:07:26,625 --> 00:07:27,416
But that's okay

233
00:07:27,416 --> 00:07:28,625
We can directly download

234
00:07:28,625 --> 00:07:30,833
gyroscope settings configured by others

235
00:07:30,833 --> 00:07:31,833
In Cyberpunk 2077

236
00:07:31,833 --> 00:07:33,500
you can touch the touchpad

237
00:07:33,500 --> 00:07:35,666
and the gyroscope will simulate mouse movement

238
00:07:35,666 --> 00:07:36,916
making aiming better

239
00:07:36,916 --> 00:07:38,833
The Satisfactory mouse and keyboard configuration

240
00:07:38,833 --> 00:07:41,833
already has over a hundred thousand hours of playtime

241
00:07:41,833 --> 00:07:43,041
The grips on the back of the Steam Controller

242
00:07:43,041 --> 00:07:44,833
have additional touch sensor strips

243
00:07:44,833 --> 00:07:46,041
called Grip Sense

244
00:07:46,041 --> 00:07:48,000
They can also be configured to trigger pause

245
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:49,666
The degree of customization is very high

246
00:07:49,666 --> 00:07:50,666
Combined with the touchpad

247
00:07:50,666 --> 00:07:52,625
I think the Steam Controller has solved

248
00:07:52,625 --> 00:07:54,708
most of the problems encountered when using a controller

249
00:07:54,708 --> 00:07:56,083
to play PC games

250
00:07:58,791 --> 00:08:00,500
Of course, all of this is based on

251
00:08:00,500 --> 00:08:03,333
All the games you want to play are on Steam.

252
00:08:03,333 --> 00:08:06,416
The Steam Controller really can only be used with Steam.

253
00:08:06,416 --> 00:08:08,291
If Steam isn't running,

254
00:08:08,291 --> 00:08:10,833
the controller isn't even recognized as a controller.

255
00:08:10,833 --> 00:08:13,291
If you want to use it to play your Epic Games Store collection,

256
00:08:13,291 --> 00:08:14,416
XGP, GOG,

257
00:08:14,416 --> 00:08:16,458
or emulator games, pirated game resources,

258
00:08:16,458 --> 00:08:18,083
by default, it simply won't work.

259
00:08:18,083 --> 00:08:20,000
Either you add them as non-Steam games,

260
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:21,875
one by one, into Steam,

261
00:08:21,875 --> 00:08:22,916
and launch them from Steam,

262
00:08:22,916 --> 00:08:25,833
or you download this open-source plugin called SISR,

263
00:08:25,833 --> 00:08:28,125
and keep Steam running in the background.

264
00:08:28,125 --> 00:08:30,000
Either way, it's quite a hassle.

265
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:30,500
Not to mention,

266
00:08:30,500 --> 00:08:33,125
it can't be used with any game console either.

267
00:08:33,125 --> 00:08:35,291
This compatibility, combined with its $100 price tag,

268
00:08:35,291 --> 00:08:38,333
makes it really hard to recommend to everyone.

269
00:08:38,458 --> 00:08:40,833
For $100, you can buy a PS5 controller,

270
00:08:40,833 --> 00:08:42,833
plus an extra Xbox controller,

271
00:08:42,833 --> 00:08:44,916
or several third-party controllers.

272
00:08:44,916 --> 00:08:46,791
And compared to the PS5 controller,

273
00:08:46,791 --> 00:08:48,583
it doesn't even have adaptive triggers.

274
00:08:48,583 --> 00:08:50,458
It's not a total win, you know.

275
00:08:50,458 --> 00:08:53,000
If you just need a controller to pair with keyboard and mouse

276
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:54,666
for playing AAA games,

277
